Document Object Model (DOM) 

Document  - HTML Document
File    - Java Class
Object - Element: States and Behaviours
Model: Data

<input type="text">

login: username password

What is the DOM?

The Document Object Model (DOM) is a programming interface for web documents. It represents the page so that programs can change the document structure, style, and content. 

JS: Add Interaction with the web page. 

DOM API: functions / methods: 

<h1 id="name"> Viyan </h1>

ctrl+shift+I -> Inspector

<h1 id="name"> Viyan </h1>
<script>
alert(document.getElementById("name"))

</script>
Output: [object HTMLHeadingElement]

In Browser: ctrl+shift+I: 
document.getElementById("name")

Change this to:
alert(document.getElementById("name").innerHTML)
document.getElementById("name").innerHTML

document.getElementById("name").innerText 

<div id="name"> Viyan </div>
<script>
alert(document.getElementById("name").innerHTML)

</script>
